This paper is about generative Visual Dialogue (VD) systems, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) techniques. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel training scheme and an adaptive multi-modal reasoning module, which involve machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques, respectively. Hence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Learning), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also likely sub-categories.
